---
export const prerender = true;
import ChapterLayout from '../layouts/ChapterLayout.astro';
import { chapters } from '../data/chapters';
import FadeInBlock from '../components/scroll/FadeInBlock';
import AccentBar from '../components/ui/AccentBar';
import Divider from '../components/ui/Divider';
import TerminalPlayground from '../components/widgets/ch7/TerminalPlayground';
import ShipIt from '../components/breaks/ShipIt';
import BreakReveal from '../components/breaks/BreakReveal';
import SharePrompt from '../components/ui/SharePrompt';

const chapter = chapters[6];
---

<ChapterLayout chapter={chapter}>

  <!-- ═══ HERO ═══ -->
  <section class="min-h-[80vh] flex flex-col items-center justify-end px-6 pb-20 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="chapter-number" style={`color: ${chapter.accent};`}>7</div>

    <div class="max-w-[680px] mx-auto text-center relative z-10">
      <FadeInBlock client:visible>
        <p class="text-[13px] italic text-subtle/60 mb-5" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">
          Chapter Seven
        </p>
      </FadeInBlock>

      <FadeInBlock client:visible delay={0.15}>
        <h1
          class="mb-8 leading-[1.08]"
          style={`font-family: var(--font-heading); color: ${chapter.accent}; font-size: clamp(2.8rem, 7vw, 4.5rem); font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.03em;`}
        >
          Mastering<br />Claude Code
        </h1>
      </FadeInBlock>

      <FadeInBlock client:visible delay={0.3}>
        <p class="text-lg md:text-xl italic text-deep/40 leading-relaxed max-w-sm mx-auto" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">
          Your AI pair programmer, from first<br />command to custom Skills.
        </p>
      </FadeInBlock>
    </div>

    <div class="absolute bottom-6 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 opacity-20 animate-pulse">
      <div class="w-px h-10 bg-deep/40"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ OPENING HOOK ═══ -->
  <section class="max-w-[680px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 pt-24 pb-16">
    <FadeInBlock client:visible>
      <p class="text-lg leading-[1.85] drop-cap" style="margin: 0;">
        There's a moment every coder remembers. You open a terminal, type a natural-language request, and watch an AI read your files, understand your architecture, write code across multiple files, run it, hit an error, fix the error, and run it again — all without you touching a single line. Claude Code isn't autocomplete. It's an <em>agentic</em> coding tool that sees your entire project, makes changes across files, executes shell commands, and iterates on its own mistakes.
      </p>
    </FadeInBlock>

    <FadeInBlock client:visible delay={0.1}>
      <p class="text-lg leading-[1.85] mt-8">
        The tool is only as good as the human steering it, though. Claude Code can write a thousand lines of perfect code in seconds — or a thousand lines of plausible-looking garbage. The difference is you.
      </p>
    </FadeInBlock>
  </section>

  <Divider accent={chapter.accent} client:load />

  <!-- ═══ THE LOOP ═══ -->
  <section class="max-w-[680px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-16">
    <FadeInBlock client:visible>
      <AccentBar color={chapter.accent} className="w-16 mb-10" client:visible />
      <h2 class="mb-8" style="font-family: var(--font-heading);">
        Specify, Generate, Verify
      </h2>
    </FadeInBlock>

    <FadeInBlock client:visible delay={0.1}>
      <p class="text-lg leading-[1.85] mb-14" style="margin-top: 0;">
        When you give Claude Code a task, it runs an agent loop: read the codebase, plan what to change, write the edits, run the code, fix whatever broke. It might cycle through that loop three, five, ten times — all in seconds. Your job isn't to write every line anymore. It's to <strong>specify</strong> what to build, let the AI <strong>generate</strong> it, and then <strong>verify</strong> that it's actually right. Most beginners skip that last step. They see code appear, it looks reasonable, and they move on. Don't be that person. Generated code is a first draft. Your verification is the edit that makes it publishable.
      </p>
    </FadeInBlock>

    <FadeInBlock client:visible delay={0.2}>
      <p class="text-lg leading-[1.85] mb-14">
        The secret weapon is the <code>CLAUDE.md</code> file — drop it in your project root and Claude Code reads it at the start of every session. Your tech stack, naming conventions, style rules, testing expectations — all encoded once so you never repeat yourself. It's context engineering applied to coding.
      </p>
    </FadeInBlock>

    <FadeInBlock client:visible delay={0.3}>
      <div class="insight-box">
        <p style={`font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 700; color: ${chapter.accent}; margin: 0 0 0.5rem;`}>The goal isn't to write every line — it's to understand every line.</p>
        <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.75; margin: 0;">
          If you can't read the code Claude generates, you can't verify it. The best Claude Code users aren't the ones who generate the most code — they're the ones who ask the best questions and catch the subtlest bugs.
        </p>
      </div>
    </FadeInBlock>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ WIDGET BRIDGE ═══ -->
  <section class="max-w-[680px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 pt-4 pb-8">
    <FadeInBlock client:visible>
      <p class="text-lg leading-[1.85] text-center mx-auto italic text-deep/50" style="max-width: 45ch; font-family: var(--font-body);">
        See the loop in action. Type a request and watch Claude Code work.
      </p>
    </FadeInBlock>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ THE WIDGET ═══ -->
  <section id="terminal-playground" class="max-w-[900px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-8">
    <TerminalPlayground client:visible />
  </section>

  <Divider accent={chapter.accent} client:load />

  <SharePrompt text="This chapter on Claude Code is wild — watched an AI pair programmer think through a problem, write code, and debug itself. The future of coding is here." client:visible />

  <!-- ═══ SEND-OFF ═══ -->
  <section class="max-w-[680px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-24">
    <FadeInBlock client:visible>
      <div class="pull-quote" style={`border-color: ${chapter.accent}; max-width: 50ch; margin: 0 auto 2rem;`}>
        Claude Code isn't writing code for you — it's writing code with you.
      </div>
    </FadeInBlock>

    <FadeInBlock client:visible delay={0.1}>
      <p class="text-lg leading-[1.85] text-center mx-auto" style="max-width: 55ch;">
        One conversation can handle one task. But real projects have dozens. Next: how to break big ambitions into pieces AI can actually execute.
      </p>
    </FadeInBlock>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ BREAK ═══ -->
  <section id="break" class="py-16 px-6" style="background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--color-cream) 0%, rgba(123,97,255,0.06) 15%, rgba(123,97,255,0.06) 85%, var(--color-cream) 100%);">
    <div class="max-w-[900px] mx-auto">
      <BreakReveal accentColor="#7B61FF" toolName="Ship It" client:visible>
        <ShipIt client:visible />
      </BreakReveal>
    </div>
  </section>

</ChapterLayout>
